author: Barry K
title: ​This Huevos Rancheros Recipe Is a Breakfast Game-Changer
text:
pinch of salt, ground black pepper, and cumin 
How to Make It: In a food processor, combine tomatoes, onion, garlic, chipotle pepper, cilantro, and juice of half the lime. Pulse until salsa is blended but slightly chunky. In a bowl, combine beans, cumin, and remaining lime juice. Add salt and pepper to taste. Lightly mash beans. In a greased nonstick skillet over medium heat, crack in eggs and cook until whites have set but yolks are runny. In another skillet over medium heat, toast tortillas a minute per side. Spread beans on tortillas and top with eggs and salsa. 
Per serving: 390 calories, 13g fat, 52g carbs, 5g fiber, 21g protein
